Five East Bay police departments are set to receive federal grants to help reduce gun violence, improve community involvement with police and beef up youth outreach.

The grants come under the auspices of the U.S. Department of Justice’s Office of Community Oriented Policing Services Hiring Program, which gives grants every year to hundreds of law enforcement agencies across the United States to hire new officers.
